COLOMBO - Sri Lanka's cricket board on Friday announced that South Africa will visit in September for three one-day internationals and three Twenty20s behind closed doors. The three ODI's will start on 2 September while the T20 tournament will begin on 10 September, Sri Lanka Cricket said in a statement. Schedule: Day-night ODI games: 2, 4 and 7 September. T20 night matches: 10, 12 and 14 September. All six matches to be played at the 35,000-capacity Premadasa Stadium in Colombo without spectators. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android device.